# Command check-git-repos

## What does this command do:

Walks $HOME recursively, finds every git repository, and reports any that are out of sync with their remote or have a dirty working tree. All repos are checked concurrently, making it significantly faster than an equivalent shell loop.

## Installed from

For Fedora install using: curl -Lo ~/bin/check-git-repos https://github.com/kevinpinscoe/tools/releases/download/check-git-repos-v1.3.0/check-git-repos-linux-amd64 && chmod +x ~/bin/check-git-repos
For Raspberry Pi install using: curl -Lo ~/bin/check-git-repos https://github.com/kevinpinscoe/tools/releases/download/check-git-repos-v1.3.0/check-git-repos-linux-arm64 && chmod +x ~/bin/check-git-repos
For Mac install using: curl -Lo ~/bin/check-git-repos https://github.com/kevinpinscoe/tools/releases/download/check-git-repos-v1.3.0/check-git-repos-darwin-arm64 && chmod +x ~/bin/check-git-repos

## Command path

For Fedora run: /home/kinscoe/bin/check-git-repos
For Raspberry Pi run: ~/bin/check-git-repos
For Mac run: ~/bin/check-git-repos

## Command documentation

Docs can be found at https://github.com/kevinpinscoe/tools/tree/main/check-git-repos-source

## Command options

check-git-repos              # scan and report (with spinner in interactive terminals)
check-git-repos --batch-mode # scan without spinner (for systemd/cron)
check-git-repos --version    # print version and exit
check-git-repos --help       # print this help

## Output status values

AHEAD                    # local commits not yet pushed
BEHIND                   # remote commits not yet pulled
AHEAD and BEHIND (diverged) # both ahead and behind
STAGED                   # changes indexed but not committed
UNSTAGED                 # tracked files with uncommitted edits
UNTRACKED                # files not yet added to git

## Ignore file

# Create ~/.config/check-git-repos-source/ignore.txt to skip repo subtrees
# One path per line; ~ is expanded; lines beginning with # are comments
~/archives/playbook      # example: skip a subtree
